By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it  has confirmed 1,138 fresh infections and have so far discharged a total of 108,657 patients since the index case was reported in February 27, 2020 in the country. The new confirmed cases brought the total confirmed cases to 134,690 across the 36 states of the federation including the FCT, the health agency further stated in its report released via it’s twitter handle account. The NCDC also informed that the newly confirmed infections were recorded from these underlisted states: Lagos-377; FCT-172; Plateau-86; Kano-84Edo-60; Osun-47; Nasarawa-41; Imo-40;Rivers-36; Niger and Oyo-32 each; Borno-29. Other states where infections were recorded are: Kaduna-27; Delta-18; Kwara-17; Cross River-9; Ekiti-8; Bauchi and Ogun-7 each;Sokoto-6 and Bayelsa-3. The health agency regrettably announced that 1,618 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case in the country. It further gave the breakdown of total confirmed cases as shown below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The latest COVID-19 report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has it that Lagos State, the epicentre of the novel virus, accounted for 642 infections as the health agency confirmed 1,074 new cases on Monday. According to the report released via… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Rivers state on Saturday led the COVID-19 table with 42 cases as  the Nigeria Centre for Disease  Control confirmed 160 fresh infections in the country. Releasing the report via it's twitter handle, the NCDC said total confirmed cases